reviewText:
The story follows one Chicago Latino gang of poor drug dealers, particularly the lives of three members who are torn between being a brother in arms gangster and taking care of people they love. The film boasts one of the worst drive-by shooting with a vintage Pontiac. The ending has a twist that wasn't well developed. There wasn't much of a story plot. 2 1/2 stars

Guide: F-bomb, sex, nudity ( Lizabeth Silva + others)
This was not a bad movie, but we do need more good urban latino films like this to be made

La movie me llego broken por lo tanto no pude mirarla entonces no puedo opinar hacerca de la movie. tuve que regresar la movie. Para la siguiente mejor compro una nueva. Esque la anterior la compre usada.

This is a very good movie and enjoyed the plot lines, it is about reality in the Hood. Wasn't sure if i would like it when ordering it based on reading about it, but it gets the intended message across.

This was an excellent movie. I loved the storyline. Definitely worth checking out.  It was about a gang in Chicago, and one of the guys was "going soft" in their eyes because of a woman he loved. Getting out of a gang brought difficulty in his life. Again, this movie had a wonderful storyline. Check this movie out.
